Events.RelatedDescription: Merged pull request "Move business logic out of ViewModels related to upcoming embedded icon changes" (#7364) at NuGet/NuGetGallery
Events.RelatedBody:
Addresses https://github.com/NuGet/Engineering/issues/2599.

`ViewModelExtensions` class was added and all the initialization code from the constructors was moved there. All the properties of affected VMs were made read-write where possible, so controllers are now have freedom to set the to whatever they like without potentially complicated (in case of deep inheritance trees) changes to VM constructors.
`BasicUserViewModel` class was introduced to be used instead of passing `User` model into VMs, helpers were updated to accommodate to the change.

Events.RelatedBody:
### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.

* Repository file contents
* Package names / package versions

Events.RelatedDescription: Opened issue "Add page for managing site admins" (#7388) at NuGet/NuGetGallery
Events.RelatedBody: Site admins should be able to manage the list of site admins. Previously, we had a database editor that could be used to add/remove admins. After it was removed, adding or removing an admin requires database access. We should be able to do this from the UI.

Events.RelatedDescription: Merged pull request "Add page for managing site admins" (#7387) at NuGet/NuGetGallery
Events.RelatedBody:
Currently, we don't have a UI that allows us to manage site admins. Previously, we had the database editor, which we would use to do this, but we recently removed it. As a result, now, whenever we need to onboard someone to the team, we have to gain database access and make a SQL query to make them a site admin.

This PR adds a simple UI to the admin section of the site that allows us to easily and quickly manage site admins.

# Link to page in Admins index

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18014088/62084147-70e6be80-b20d-11e9-93a6-2f611dd8cc48.png)

# Site Admins page

Events.RelatedDescription: Opened issue "Remove NuGet.Build.Tasks.Pack.Sdk2x package" (#8403) at NuGet/Home
Events.RelatedBody:
As there is no more NuGet insertion into SDK 2.x, there is no need to generate the NuGet.Build.Tasks.Pack.Sdk2x package in our code.
We should remove related code.
Related issue https://github.com/NuGet/Home/issues/8043

  <!--Include the stylecop analyzers for the release build -->

  <PropertyGroup Condition="'$(Configuration)|$(Platform)'=='Release|AnyCPU'">
    <CodeAnalysisRuleSet>..\_solutionItems\StyleCop.Adapter.ruleset</CodeAnalysisRuleSet>
